<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–649: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Butler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-06T15:00:00-05:00">October 6,
                                    1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:22 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>338. In reply to my question, Hevia<note n="81" xml:id="d110fn81">Carlos
                                Hevia, Cuban Minister of State.</note> told me yesterday Cuba will
                            follow lead of US in its relations with China. He said no question of
                            Cuba’s recognizing Chinese Communist government at present time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Butler</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>